 is to examine how philosophy can be applied to the betterment of the everyday lives of citizens in cities in the West and Asia. The papers' comparative approach, between East and West, and ancient and modern, lead to a greater understanding of the challenges facing cities in the twenty-first century, and, by looking to past examples, suggest ways of addressing them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aPhilosophy. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aPhilosophy, Cities, Citizenship, Care, Becoming.1 aAugust, Karan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorgmann, Katharina M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBracken, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBracken, Gregory, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCahyadhuha, Brandon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGao, Yun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHastangka,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKresse, Klaas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLacertosa, Massimiliano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitão Martins, Luiz Paulo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Ian R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusdy, Sri Teddy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShiqiao, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSneep, Deirdre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTemple, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator